Victoria's Seasonal Pollen Story

Our city's changing seasons shape how pollen spreads. Understanding these shifts helps residents plan better and breathe easier.

1

Spring

Sept - Nov

Highest pollen spread, about 60% more than other seasons

2

Summer

Dec - Feb

Moderate pollen levels, around 40% dispersion

3

Fall

Mar - May

Lowest pollen spread, about 35%, offering natural relief

4

Winter

Jun - Aug

Moderate spread, winds rise but damp air holds pollen down

Quick Tip

Shower and change clothes as soon as you come indoors.

This helps wash pollen off your skin and hair, and prevents it from spreading onto your bedding and furniture, reducing nighttime symptoms.
